    <div class="AssessmentProblem.identifier">102641</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">RestrictedConstructedResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>A recipe for 1 batch of spice mix says,&#xA0;&#x201C;Combine 3 teaspoons of mustard seeds, 5 teaspoons of chili powder, and 1 teaspoon of salt.&#x201D; How many batches are represented by the diagram? Explain or show your reasoning.</p>

<p><img class="h-max-height--6-lines" src="/image_files/29469.png" /></p>

<p>&#xA0;<presentation-tag data-tag-title="1 INCH" data-tree-code="MS_pi" data-tree-node-id="243962" data-tree-ref-id="215" src="/presentation_tags/4.tag"></presentation-tag> <presentation-tag data-tag-title="1 INCH" data-tree-code="Accel6_8" data-tree-node-id="260635" data-tree-ref-id="218" src="/presentation_tags/4.tag"></presentation-tag></p>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><p>The diagram&#xA0;represents 3 batches of spice mix. It shows 3 times the amount of&#xA0;each ingredient in the recipe:&#xA0;9 teaspoons of mustard (<span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="6630">\(3 \boldcdot 3\)</span>), 15 teaspoons of chili powder (<span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="13434">\(3 \boldcdot 5\)</span>), and 3 teaspoons of salt (<span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="43109">\(3 \boldcdot 1\)</span>).</p>
</div>
